name: Christopher Lindsey
text: Jim is knowledgeable and really funny.  He is focused on the work. My hydraulics come here to be repaired. I wouldn't even consider going any other place.

name: Krash Hamilton
text: Great people that are dedicated to perfection.

name: Blake Powers
text: Price  gouging at its best!!!  They had one guy working 5 hours of wo $1900!  On top of that they were supposed to meet us at 8:00 AM on Saturday morning and showed up at 11. It cost us a whole day of work.  Save yourself by not making this mistake !  The job should’ve been $400.  I’m taking this to the better business bureau.

name: Eddie Kiser
text: Great people to have working for you. Sam was an excellent help after hours got us back going quick. No one eles will get my business while working in this area.

resp.text: Thank you.  I will tell Sam of your kind words!

name: Bill Yancy
text: Just excellent service. I left my backhoe's leaking arm cylinder here and JimPam had it ready for me in 2 days, and at a better price for new seals than I've EVER gotten. It works like brand new now, Jim's experience speaks for itself

resp.text: Thank you! I'm glad we were able to get you up and running quickly!

name: Chuck Linderman
text:
They do jobs nobody else can. The Hydraulic manifold on my Russian Belarus 250AS was in need of an overhaul. Every where I took it said trash it, buy another or wouldn't even consider attempting to rebuild it.
Jim was able to do the job for a fair price and saved me a lot of time and money. Check them out !!

resp.text: Thanks Chuck! It was a pleasure meeting you, and thank you for the comment!

name: Robyn Z
text: Excellent, friendly, professional, and very clean shop. And fast services. I won't go anywhere else for my hydraulic services. Thanks Jim your awesome!

name: franklin mitchell
text: Check with Jim before you buy the rebuilt kit from dealer. A friend told me about  Jimpam. Now ill tell all in need of repair where to go. Excellent  experience

resp.text: Thank you! We are usually able to buy parts, seals, etc for less than what our customers could buy the item for.  We pass that savings on to our customers.  Thanks for your review!

name: Mike Smith
text: Totally ruined a hydralic lift unit.Still to this day unable to use! Should have been told but i guess they were more into money than customer.

name: Mike S
text: Best tech in the southeast. If no one else can do it, Jim can!

resp.text: Thank you for taking the time to say!  We appreciate your business!

name: Jennifer Hurley
text: Very unfriendly people. Would not recommend this company to anyone. Totally unprofessional!!!

name: Project 97
text: I like Grainger and have never had a problem until now. I just tried to call the mobile location and they woman that answered the phone said that there is no way to be transferred to an exact store. If that is true that’s the craziest thing I’ve ever heard. I asked her so if you can’t transfer me to them, then just give me the number to them and I’ll call. Her response was the store doesn’t have a number. I asked, so there is absolutely no way possible to communicate or get in touch with anyone at that location? And she said that’s correct. It has been that way for years she said. It blew my mind. Truly the craziest thing I have heard in quite a while.

resp.text: Hi, Chris. Thank you for the feedback. Our local branches do not take calls, allowing them to assist our customers who walk in the door. Our customer service team can be reached at 1(800)472-4643 and are available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. They have access to the same information to ensure you receive the right information when you need it. ^Amber, Grainger Social Team

name: Stacy Upshaw
text: I was surprised at how good the customer service is over the telephone, very helpful looking up part numbers and the shipping was very fast

resp.text: We're very happy we could help, Stacy! Thank you for sharing this and thanks for choosing Grainger!

name: Rock
text:
Not open on Saturday but the Grainger website says it IS open. It is NOT open on Saturday. I just drove a freaking hour to come buy work boots.
Why not be open on Saturday anyway? We work monday-friday in the normal world when we'd go here.

name: Goddbod. Junya “iceberg” Winston
text: nice neighborhood..

name: Wes Allday
text: Nice selection in inventory, staff is helpful with finding/ordering needed parts. Prices can be a bit steep.

name: Doug Fleming
text: Why is this the only electrical supplier that WONT let you speak to a local store without jumping through hoops?

resp.text: Hi, Doug. Thank you for the feedback. Our local branches do not take calls, allowing them to assist our customers who walk in the door. Our customer service team is set up to assist our Customers 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, and has access to the same information to ensure you receive the right information when you need it. ^Amber, Grainger Social Team

name: Jared Winton
text: If you were to look up the definition of customer service it would simply read Total Hose! The people that work there will go out of their way to make sure you leave not only with more knowledge about what you are repairing/replacing but also the correct parts to repair/replace the problem. They completely made an OEM installed product better with their knowledge and skill. On top of all that it was super affordable. Highly recommend Total Hose for any of your air/hydraulic/water lines or maintenance.

name: Jessica Reece
text: The guys in here are always helpful. They can always find what I need. So appreciative of the fact that they'll build whatever hose we need while I wait. They are a lifesaver.

name: Mark Burch
text: Very helpful place. They patiently took the time to help me figure out what I needed for my application and explain things to me. I'll be returning for sure.

name: David Cady
text: Knowledgeable, fast, and very skilled at building/routing hydraulic lines

name: Patrick
text: My go to place for hydraulic hoses and hose fittings.  Always quick to custom manufacture what I need when necessary.

name: Jeremy Nichols
text: Excellent service

name: Timothy Gulley
text: Great place to come for all your hose needs come on by and let us fix you up

name: Poppi3579
text: Great place, Great Service.  Thanks Tim

name: Sam Cook
text: The older man at the front desk is rude and is hard to deal with every time me or any other of my employees go into the store needing something. the previos review before mine says this has been dealt with and obviously it hasn't been or this wouldn't be an issue 1 year later.

resp.text: We greatly apologize for the disappointing visit.  We have talked to the store personal and the manager will address this issue.  I hope you will give AHP an other opportunity to make a better impression.

name: Joshua Wagnon
text: Always have what I need in stock with quick in and out service. Little pricey but you get what you pay for with a knowledgeable staff and quality parts. I always recommend them when someone is in need of hose related parts.

name: Shawn Holmes
text: Need someone else working up front that can actually help instead of being smart.

resp.text:
Shawn,
We greatly apologize for your experience at the store.  AHP strives for excellent customer service. This issue will be addressed immediately.

name: Daniel Hall
text: Very helpful staff. They figured out what I needed even though I wasn't sure. I explained the best I could what type of hose I needed and they figured it out from there. I took the Hose to the job and it fit perfectly

name: Patrick
text: I use TotalHose in Decatur and Huntsville regularly.  They are the only source for hydraulic hoses and parts that I trust in huntsville and decatur.  Scott and team do a wonderful job.

name: Jon Madrigal
text: I got hosed and was happy about it

name: J C
text: Good selection but high prices on most items. However the have parts that you can’t get elsewhere. I need some aluminum angle and they beat Home Depot and Lowes prices by far.

name: Paul Streeter
text: Great helpful advice on my project, thanks

resp.text: Thanks for the nice review! Our goal is to always be the best partner possible to our customers. Glad to hear we were able to help you out! ^Paul, Grainger Social Team

name: Jack Lloyd
text: Worst customer service.  Having people wait for hour to get service is unacceptable.

resp.text: Jack, we're sorry your Grainger experience wasn't satisfactory and would like to look into it further. Please email our customer service team at social@grainger.com with your name, the branch you visited, and a brief description of your experience. ^Paul, Grainger Social Team

text: Store personnel is extremely helpful and friendly. Sometimes the parts I order aren’t immediately available but they can usually get it in next day. Prices are somewhat competitive but I understand I’m shopping at an industrial supply house.

resp.text:
Thanks for the nice review! Our goal is to always be the best partner possible to our customers. Glad to hear we were able to help you out!
^Paul, Grainger Social Team

name: Mike Heard
text: I took a long list of tools I needed to purchase to the local store here in Huntsville, AL. The took the list and told me it would be a couple of days.  Here it is two weeks latter and I have heard nothing.  To top that, when I look to find their business phone number it is the corporate phone number and they cannot give you the store number.  I will not attempt to do business with them again.  If there was a zero star I would have selected it.  What poor customer service.

resp.text: Mike, we're sorry your Grainger branch experience wasn't satisfactory and would like to look into it further. Please email our customer service team at social@grainger.com with your name, the branch you visited, and a brief description of your experience (including order number, account number, or any other information you feel may be helpful). Thanks for the nice review, Thomas! Our goal is to always be the best partner possible to our customers. Glad to hear we were able to help you out!

name: Shane Gann
text: I need an electric motor, I called the store and got a call center, the lady knew nothing about parts, read her multiple parts numbers off the motor and the fan it was attached to. She finally said we are just going to have to call tech support.......really? I just need to know if the motor is in the store before I drive all the way over there.

name: Ray Blackwell
text: Great personal staff and the Yard Man went above and beyond the call of duty to help me to cover the exhaust system from the weather. I've been doing business with COWIN for many years. All locations are in the great state of alabama. Service and sales good place for your needs on equipment.

name: Schubert Enterprises, LLC
text: Cowin Equipment is a business that involves working with great people, and easy to work with. We really have enjoyed working with this company and Daniel Lawrence.

text: The service manager is AWESOME!! If you need to rent heavy equipment this is the place!!

This family company runs about 4 generation's deep. I highly recommend their quality workmanship and on point dignostics with honesty.

name: Amanda
text:
Great Company. Our compnay has been using C and P for years to work on our shuttle buses and they always give us straight forward answers and get the work done quickly.
Highly recommend this company.

name: John Martin
text: Alternator failure on my RV while in Tuscaloosa over the weekend and I needed it fixed Monday morning to return home. I called C & P and they said "bring it over."   Chance started the work and Angelo helped me get the right part.  Done in an hour and back on the road home.  Competent, Efficient, and Professional.  Thanks, C & P for saving me the headache and stress.

name: Barry Fields
text: Great company and reliable!

name: Pretty BlueBird
text: The guy was really helpful and polite. It was a pleasure doing business with him!

name: David Ware
text: Great fast and experienced staff. I've been all over town searching for this particular long bolt and nut. They found it within 3 minutes.

text: Awesome always. They can manufacture/repair any steel line or hose line in minutes while you wait. This should be your first stop.

name: surles william
text: Good service

name: Chad Jackson
text: Very helpful,  they take the time to help with your project.  They are usually busy with loads of customers.  They make hydraulic hose, air hose, tubing and carry most nuts and bolt for industrial use. They dont carry automobile specific bolts. They do have dot air brake fittings and hose.

name: Patrick
text: Was there last Thursday for a job in town and they were able to help with ease.  not only do they custom make hoses but they also have a great too selection
